ksdk:manifest.name: SDK version 2.4.1 package for LPCXpresso54114 board
ksdk:manifest.brief: This is SDK version 2.4.1 manifest file. It describes the content of the SDK version 2.4.1 package for LPCXpresso54114 board and additional settings for tools that support SDK version 2.4.1

board.name: LPCXPRESSO54114-AGMP03
board.description: Sensor Toolbox Development Platform for FXLS8962, FXAS21002C, MAG3110 and MPL3115 10-Axis Solution

specific.content:
Demonstration Kits (FRDM-STBC-AGMP03 Sensor Shield Development Board with LPCXPRESSO54114 Board):
  • Enables an ‘Out of the box’ Sensor demonstrations using the Freedom Sensor Toolbox – CE software.
  • Enables quick and easy visualization of 10-Axis (3 Axis Accelerometer, 3 Axis Magnetometer, 3 Axis Gyroscope and 1-Axis Pressure) sensor data and results.

board.name: LPCXPRESSO54114-AGM01
board.description: Sensor Toolbox Development Platform for FXAS21002C and FXOS8700C 9-Axis Solution

specific.content:
Custom Kit (FRDMSTBC-AGM01 Sensor Shield Development Board with LPCXPRESSO54114 Board):
  • Enables 'Out of the Box’ demonstrations using the ISSDK and Freedom Sensor Toolbox – CE software on LPCXPRESSO54114 board with FRDMSTBC-AGM01 sensor shield board.
  • Enables quick and easy visualization of 9-Axis (3 Axis Gyroscope + 6-Axis E-compass) sensor data and results.

board.name: LPCXpresso54114
board.description: The LPCXpresso family of boards provides a powerful and flexible development system for NXP®'s Cortex-M MCUs

specific.content:
The LPCXpresso family of boards provides a powerful and flexible development system for NXP®'s Cortex-M MCUs. The LPCXpresso54114 board has been developed by NXP to enable evaluation of and prototyping with the LPC54110 family of MCUs and its low power features make it as easy as possible to get started with your project.
LPCXpresso™ is a low-cost development platform available from NXP supporting NXP's ARM-based microcontrollers. The platform is comprised of a simplified Eclipse-based IDE and low-cost target boards which include an attached JTAG debugger. LPCXpresso is an end-to-end solution enabling embedded engineers to develop their applications from initial evaluation to final production.

board.name: LPCXpresso54114-OM13588
board.description: USB Type-C Shield Board for Kinetis Freedom Board

specific.content: The USB Type-C shield board combined with a Kinetis Power Delivery SDK allows a system designer to tether a USB Type-C connector to any Kinetis development platform.

device.name: LPC54114
device.description: The LPC5411x are ARM Cortex-M4 based microcontrollers for embedded applications.

specific.content:
The LPC5411x are ARM Cortex-M4 based microcontrollers for embedded applications. These devices include an ARM Cortex-M0+ coprocessor, up to 192 KB of on-chip SRAM, up to 256 KB on-chip flash, full-speed USB device interface with Crystal-less operation, a DMIC subsystem with PDM microphone interface and I2S, five general-purpose timers, one SCTimer/PWM, one RTC/alarm timer, one 24-bit Multi-Rate Timer (MRT), a Windowed Watchdog Timer (WWDT), eight flexible serial communication peripherals (each of which can be a USART, SPI, or I2C interface), and one 12-bit 5.0 Msamples/sec ADC, and a temperature sensor.
The ARM Cortex-M4 is a 32-bit core that offers system enhancements such as low power consumption, enhanced debug features, and a high level of support block integration. The ARM Cortex-M4 CPU incorporates a 3-stage pipeline, uses a Harvard architecture with separate local instruction and data buses as well as a third bus for peripherals, and includes an internal prefetch unit that supports speculative branching. The ARM Cortex-M4 supports single-cycle digital signal processing and SIMD instructions. A hardware floating-point unit is integrated in the core.
The ARM Cortex-M0+ coprocessor is an energy-efficient and easy-to-use 32-bit core which is code and tool-compatible with the Cortex-M4 core. The Cortex-M0+ coprocessor offers up to 100 MHz performance with a simple instruction set and reduced code size.
